1.Title: Anomaly

2. What:
A 2D side-scrolling action-exploration game in Unity with a double-state system (Normal State and Anomaly State) that changes the environment, enemies, and gameplay rules.

3. Player Action:
The player moves, jumps, and attacks enemies while exploring levels,
switching between Normal and Anomaly states to overcome obstacles and reach the exit.

4. Unity Format:
2D physics, animator-driven character control, enemy AI scripts, and a state-based system for gameplay transformation.

5. Vertical slice:
A single 2D level where the player can move, jump, and attack one enemy, with a ring that toggles between Normal and Anomaly states. In Normal State, the player navigates a simple platform map with visible paths and a basic enemy blocking progress. When the Anomaly State is activated, the environment changes (like  hidden path appears or enemy behavior changes)

6. Core system : 
player control(move, attack, physics detection),enemy(move, attack, automatical patrol and detection)


7. One visible task before session:
Roles of player and enemgy can move and attack. There would be at least 3 different enmey. A good tilemap and some UI to indicate the player's health level. Most importantly is the clear rule to complete one level of the game.

8. Five Week Plan:
  [Week 1] implement basic logical of palyers and enemys
  [Week 2]  ui management, and success determination
  [Week 3]  double-status system(different tilemap style and rules)
  [Week 4] add different endings and more interesting storytelling.
  [Week 5] Testing\Fixs bugs\polish to reach vividly medieval style
